http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/chennai/DMK-seeks-solatium-for-victims-of-fever/article14617426.ece

Days after the spread of fever in various parts of Tiruvallur district that claimed a few lives, the DMK raised the issue in the Assembly and urged the State government to announce a compensation of Rs. 10 lakh to families of those who lost their lives to the fever.Soon after Question Hour, DMK legislator V.G. Raajendran (Tiruvallur) moved a special call attention motion in the House and brought to the notice of the government the spread of fever in the district.